# Delivery OS — deterministic line endings.
#
# The Workflow Engine (and the vendored tool templates) are VENDORED byte-for-byte
# into consuming apps and locked by a byte-exact drift gate (os-inherit engine-check),
# which hashes the WORKING-TREE bytes against canonical's working-tree bytes. If
# canonical's working tree is platform-dependent (autocrlf smudging LF->CRLF on
# Windows), the vendored bytes — and therefore the gate's expected sha-set — become
# non-deterministic across machines/CI. Pin these paths to LF so canonical's working
# tree is the SAME bytes on every platform, regardless of core.autocrlf.

# The OS-foundational Workflow Engine (vendored + drift-checked).
templates/workflow-engine/**     text eol=lf

# The vendored OS tool templates + contracts (also vendored into apps).
templates/tools/**               text eol=lf
contracts/**                     text eol=lf

# Belt-and-braces by extension for the engine/tool source kinds.
*.ts    text eol=lf
*.mts   text eol=lf
*.mjs   text eol=lf
*.sql   text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
